HEADWORD: Doab
<hw>Do"ab</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[Pers. & Hind.
<ets>do⟦amac⟧b</ets>, prop., two waters.]</ety> <def>A tongue or tract
of land included between two rivers; <as>as, the <ex>doab</ex> between
the Ganges and the Jumna</as>.</def> <mark>[India]</mark> <rj><au>Am.
Cyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
